          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="experience">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header line-safe">
          <div>
            <div class="eyebrow">What makes it feel like a retreat</div>
            <h2>The experience</h2>
          </div>
          <p>This section reads less like a booking engine and more like an invitation into the atmosphere: shared meals, warm social energy, and enough structure for Shabbos and Yom Tov to feel held well.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="amenity-grid">
          <article class="amenity-card">
            <h3>Gather beautifully</h3>
            <p>The bright dining space makes the house feel ideal for long meals, coffee, learning, and conversation without forcing a hotel vibe.</p>
            <div class="specs"><span class="spec">Shared tables</span><span class="spec">Indoor gathering</span></div>
          </article>
          <article class="amenity-card">
            <h3>Stay on site</h3>
            <p>The pool, hot tub, and game room mean the property already has enough built-in activity to keep the retreat feeling full and easy.</p>
            <div class="specs"><span class="spec">Pool</span><span class="spec">Hot tub</span><span class="spec">Game room</span></div>
          </article>
          <article class="amenity-card">
            <h3>Feel close to nature</h3>
            <p>Being near Mt. Snow and close to the North Branch Deerfield River helps the event feel outdoorsy and grounded even when most of the weekend happens at the house.</p>
            <div class="specs"><span class="spec">Near Mt. Snow</span><span class="spec">River nearby</span></div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="details">
      <div class="container detail-grid">
        <article class="detail-card">
          <div class="eyebrow">Retreat overview</div>
          <h3>How this page should speak</h3>
          <p>This is not trying to be the rental listing itself. It is the Hamsa Nomads layer placed over the property: a warm, social, observance-aware weekend where the house is the setting and the people are the point.</p>
          <p>The language can be part practical and part emotional. It should help guests understand what kind of event this is, what the house offers, what the rooming energy is like, and what kind of people they can imagine joining.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom:0;">Because this is the pre-booking version, it leaves out sign-up and payment and focuses on clarity, mood, and trust.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="detail-card">
          <div class="eyebrow">Good information to include</div>
          <h3>What people usually want to know</h3>
          <ul class="clean">
            <li>What kind of crowd the event is for</li>
            <li>Whether it is Shabbos and kosher friendly</li>
            <li>What the house itself looks and feels like</li>
            <li>Whether there is enough to do on site</li>
            <li>How close it is to local nature and attractions</li>
            <li>Whether the event feels social without being chaotic</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="container detail-grid">
        <article class="detail-card">
          <div class="eyebrow">Example weekend rhythm</div>
          <h3>Sample flow</h3>
          <div class="schedule-list">
            <div class="schedule-item">
              <div class="schedule-day">Arrival</div>
              <div>
                <strong>Settle in and meet people.</strong>
                <p class="small">Guests arrive, get roomed, explore the house, see the pool and shared spaces, and ease into the tone of the weekend.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="schedule-item">
              <div class="schedule-day">Before Shabbos</div>
              <div>
                <strong>Property time and preparation.</strong>
                <p class="small">A slower lead-in with hanging out on site, optional nearby exploring, food prep, and transitioning into Yom Tov / Shabbos mode.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="schedule-item">
              <div class="schedule-day">Shabbos / Yom Tov</div>
              <div>
